West Nile fever, Turkey
-----------------------
Information received on [and dated] 4 Sep 2014 from Prof Dr Irfan Erol, director general of food and control, Directorate of Food and Control, Ministry of Food, Agriculture and Livestock, Ankara, Turkey

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 19 Aug 2014
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 2 Sep 2014
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: December 2013
Manifestation of disease: clinical infection
Causal agent: West Nile virus
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks: Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: TJK Karacabey Pansiyon Hara Mudurlugu, Bursa
Date of start of the outbreak: 19 Aug 2014
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Equidae / 300 / 1 / 1 / 0 / 0

Outbreak statistics: [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / morbidity rate / mortality rate / case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Equidae / 0.33 / 0.33 / 100 / 0.33
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: vectors
Epidemiological comments: monitoring activities are carried on. Samples have been sent to the Experimental Zooprophylactic Institute of Abruzzo and Molise "G. Caporale" (IZSAM) for confirmation.

Control measures
Measures applied: control of arthropods; quarantine; screening; zoning; disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s); no vaccination; no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Etlik Central Veterinary Control and Research Institute (national laboratory) / Equidae / real-time PCR / 2 Sep 2014 / Positive
Etlik Central Veterinary Control and Research Institute (national laboratory) / Equidae / reverse transcription-polymerase chain reaction (RT-PCR) / 2 Sep 2014 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

